README
r267 - Render based on Vulkan API
Simple renderer with main task made more with less code.

Planed struct:
base - only base functional from Vulkan to init and render.
scene - additional functional like camera, loader for models
vector - basic api for vector draw.
toolbar - toolbar api.


R267 Format for models specification v1.0 from 19.05.17
Example of file:
R267_MAGIC_NUMBER = 0x26700000 - uint32   								// Begin of file
NUM_MESHES        = ?          - uint32   								// Number of meshes in file
R267_MESH         = 0x26701000 - uint32   								// Begin of mesh
MESH_SIZE         = ?          - uint64                                 // Mesh size in bytes from begin to end without that 
NAME_MESH_SIZE    = ?          - uint32   								// Size of mesh name
NAME_MESH         = ?          - NAME_MESH_SIZE*char 					// Name of mesh
MESH_VB           = 0x26701001 - uint32                                 // Begin of vertex buffer
MESH_VB_SIZE      = ?          - uint32                                 // Number of vertexes
VERTEXES          = ?          - MESH_VB_SIZE*sVertex           		// Array of vertexes
MESH_IB           = 0x26701002 - uint32                                 // Begin of index buffer
MESH_IB_SIZE      = ?          - uint32                                 // Numbers of indexes (Not triangle)
INDEXES           = ?          - MESH_IB_SIZE*uint      				// Array of indexes
... Next R267_MESH and so also

R267 Material format materials contain data as json, that made for simple read and modify data
SCENE {
	NAME_MESH {
		diffuse_tex : "$filename",
		roughness   : "$float",
		albedo      : "$albedo"
	},
	ANOTHER_NAME {
		...
	}
}